communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In February of this year, I was denied entry to Canada in part because there's "a warrant for someone using  or with the same name" as mine-Nathan Sestack. Obviously mine is not a common name though online on the website Linktin there is a "Nathan Sestak" in Ohio. That person doesn't have a "c" in their last name though.  When I called the ranger station in northern most Vermont the next day seeking further explanation I was told to "file a freedom of information request" twice by an officer attendant of that station.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Nathan Sestack

To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the California Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

All audits of City of Huntington Park from 2017 to the present.
All communications between your agency and the City of Huntington Park from 2019 to the present, about Huntington Park's finances.

If there is any document explaining why Huntington Park is not listed on the Auditor's Local Government High Risk website at all anymore for fiscal years 2019-20, 20-21, I would like that too. Or someone can just explain why Huntington park went from the third worst City in California in fiscal year 2018-19, to not even being a pull-down option more recently.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 10 calendar days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Annette Morasch
